The paper deals with video content analysis and smart surveillance applications, which are commonly studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. The use of multispectral cameras and stereo registration also suggests a focus on multispectral imaging (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the use of dynamic priors and higher order terms, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
